-- Polish Stocks: Grupa Lotos, PKN Orlen, Petrolinvest Were Active
-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 2012-01-09T17:19:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/polish-stocks-jastrzebska-lotos-pkn-orlen-petrolinvest-move.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  closed at the
lowest level in three weeks, retreating 30.72, or 1.4 percent,
to 2,126.71 in Warsaw.  The  Warsaw Stock Exchange  was closed on Jan. 6 for a public
holiday.  The following were among the active equities on the Polish
market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Petrolinvest SA (OIL)   sank 9.9 percent to 2.81 zloty,
falling for the first time in three days. Shareholders of the
company that’s drilling for oil in Kazakhstan will vote on Jan.
31 on increasing capital by 400 million zloty ($113 million) to
600 million zloty, Petrolinvest said in a regulatory statement.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN)  , Poland’s biggest oil company, lost 2
percent to 33.56 zloty and  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  , the second-
largest refiner, declined 3.8 percent to 21.45 zloty. Oil
dropped as German and French leaders met in an attempt to revive
growth in the euro region.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw 
